text: Wilkerson Place is a historic house in Giles County, Tennessee, U.S.. It was built in the 1830s. By 1847, it belonged to Allen Wilkerson, a settler from North Carolina. The porch was built in 1857. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since October 23, 1986. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Tennessee Category:Federal architecture in Tennessee Category:Greek Revival architecture in Tennessee Category:Houses completed in 1830 Category:Houses in Giles County, Tennessee
